    <string name="bmr_tee_info">
        Basal metabolic rate (BMR) specifies the energy we use for life functions such as brain functions, work of heart and lungs,
        cell replacement, digestion of food and nutrients.
        \n
        \nTotal Energy Expenditure (TEE) is how much calories we burn each day,
        combining BMR and physical activity. TEE represents how many calories we should consume each day, while maintaining the same weight.
        \n
        \nThe three physical activity levels:
        \n- Light - people who do not engage in physical activities often and their work is not physical.
        \n- Moderate - people who have more physical jobs or spend their free time in an active way, for example moderate activity of 1h/day.
        \n- Vigorous - people with physical jobs and vigorous daily activities.
    </string>
